<h3>Algorithm</h3>
<p>At runtime Book!t builds an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_(mathematics)">undirected graph</a> in memory then traverses it to find a shortest path between you and available rooms, by using classic <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dijkstra's_algorithm">Dijkstra's algorithm.</a></p>
<p>As mentioned, capacity is also taken into consideration. Book!t uses the following formula to calculate a score for each available room:</p>
<p style="font-weight:bold">
score = distance + (attendee – capacity)2
</p>
<p>Finally all results with scores will be sorted in ascending order. DONE.</p>

